                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13631822" author="markrmiller@gmail.com" created="Mon, 15 Apr 2013 16:20:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This patch has the OverseerCollectionProcessor send a new remove collection cmd to the Overseer work queue after asking each SolrCore to unload itself.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13631826" author="markrmiller@gmail.com" created="Mon, 15 Apr 2013 16:21:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In the future, if we started shipping with no cores out of the box and required use of the collections api, the overseer could be more intelligent here I think - for example, if you removed a collection and then some instances came back that still had it, the Overseer could tell those instances to unload now stale SolrCores rather than starting them.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13653860" author="thetaphi" created="Fri, 10 May 2013 10:33:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Closed after release.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
